<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
<head>
  <title>Test that an absolute does not provide a break opportunity within an inline</title>
  <link rel="author" title="Mike Bremford" href="http://bfo.com"/>
  <link rel="help" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/visuren.html#absolute-positioning"/>
  <link rel="match" href="../../reference/ref-filled-green-100px-square-only.html"/>
  <meta name="flags" content="ahem" />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="../../../fonts/ahem.css"/>
  <meta name="assert" contents="An absolutely positioned object does not provide a break opportunity"/>
  <style>
   .block {
       font: 50px/1 Ahem;
       color: green;
       width: 1em;
   }
   .pos {
       position: absolute;
       color: white;
   }
  </style>
 </head>
 <body>
  <p>Test passes if there is a filled green square.</p>
  <div class="block">
   AA
   A<div class="pos">A</div>A
  </div>
 </body>
</html>
